    {
        "content": "<p>The easy way to fix it is <code>NeZero n</code>, and the hard way to fix it is to make all these useful tactics like <code>omega</code> and <code>linarith</code> work for <code>PNat</code>. Right now everyone takes the easy way out.</p>",
        "id": 482601907,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1731673670
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you're at the point where you're trying to close the goal with <code>linarith</code>, you can probably just <code>cases n</code> to make the pnat go away.</p>",
        "id": 482627727,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
